<subSubSection id="B08AA848DC4DFBE98999E378A99386DA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="B02F172B3C4BE3CA8E2C996363E16C51" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="ECFC2129B1AC9401203EB5F30669B9FC" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
European, possibly 
<normalizedToken id="2702296C9760692A057FF1F3F36B3864" originalValue="boreal–mountainous">boreal-mountainous</normalizedToken>
. The species was described from the Italian Alps (
<bibRefCitation id="4CC9EBA59221147DABF7661FFB0A26E4" author="Matile, L." journalOrPublisher="Revue Franacaise d'entomologie (nouvelle serie)" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="147 - 150" title="Un Sciophila nouveau de la vallee d'Aoste (Alpes italiennes) (Diptera, Mycetophilidae)" volume="5" year="1983">Matile 1983</bibRefCitation>
) and later recorded from Great Britain (
<bibRefCitation id="FE6244A5A718EC29DC812282136B80CB" author="Chandler, P." journalOrPublisher="British Journal of Entomology and Natural History" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="77 - 89" title="Additions and changes to the British fauna of fungus gnats (Diptera: Mycetophilidae)" volume="19" year="2006">Chandler 2006</bibRefCitation>
), and from Fennoscandia: Norway (
<bibRefCitation id="36C6CFBABBBEA09B222BC1AE537DBDED" author="Okland, B." journalOrPublisher="Fauna norvegica, ser. B." pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="27 - 37" title="Mycetophilids (Diptera, Sciaroidea) from South-eastern Norway" volume="44" year="1997">
<normalizedToken id="E5A40E2E2A48123F18CE743CBDD026A8" originalValue="Økland">Okland</normalizedToken>
and Zaitzev 1997
</bibRefCitation>
), Sweden (
<bibRefCitation id="016080FFF93DD12535F207179CAA4096" author="Kjaerandsen, J." journalOrPublisher="Insect Systematics &amp; Evolution, Supplement" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" pagination="1 - 165" title="Annotated checklist of fungus gnats from Sweden (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Diadocidiidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae and Mycetophilidae)" volume="65" year="2007">Kjaerandsen et al. 2007</bibRefCitation>
) and Russian Karelia (
<bibRefCitation id="C82D132906296A32DF88FB8ACEC46987" author="Humala, A. E." editor="Gromtsev, A. N." journalOrPublisher="Karelian Research Centre RAS, Petrozavodsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Rocky landscapes of Karelian shore of the White Sea: nature peculiarities, economic management and protective measures" year="2008">Humala and Polevoi 2008</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="78DD65AF1E22ADF782C99C41339BD638" author="Polevoi, A. V." journalOrPublisher="Karelian Research Centre, Russian Academy of Sciences, Petrozavodsk" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Fungus gnats (Diptera: Bolitophilidae, Ditomyiidae, Keroplatidae, Diadocidiidae, Mycetophilidae) in Karelia." year="2000">Polevoi 2000</bibRefCitation>
). The species was included in the Finnish Red List (
<bibRefCitation id="6BE0F00396AA0F7E39A8AD854A52E7E6" author="Penttinen, J." editor="Rassi, P." journalOrPublisher="Ympaeristoeministerioe &amp; Suomen ympaeristoekeskus, Helsinki" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="The 2010 Red List of Finnish Species" year="2010">Penttinen et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
), but is here formally reported as a new species for Finland.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7270B6DE86321CFC7F8EBDE647627077" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="ecology">
<paragraph id="B08670A68255F683B32CA706DE52A235" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Ecology</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27C9C5DFAA4B0E03F3C518FB2A219F58" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
Collecting site in 
<normalizedToken id="1FF49F87B3BA15D2A699CFED563E35CB" originalValue="Törmäoja">Toermaeoja</normalizedToken>
is a stream valley with seepages and young deciduous forest. Slopes nearby are coniferous stands dominated by 
<taxonomicName id="1871DAB872922DA21EE6FD41C96C466B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ericaceae" genus="Vaccinium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Vaccinium vitis-idaea" order="Ericales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="vitis-idaea">Vaccinium vitis-idaea</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="BC801A4BA376D82A3E7F99FDAEA6B07A" class="Pinopsida" family="Pinaceae" genus="Pinus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pinus sylvestris" order="Pinales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="sylvestris">Pinus sylvestris</taxonomicName>
. Collecting site in 
<normalizedToken id="319065ADFE198DB1D8842434817CB631" originalValue="Värriö">Vaerrioe</normalizedToken>
is a headwater stream surrounded by pristine spruce and pine forest. The male specimen from Savonranta was collected from a decaying aspen (
<taxonomicName id="3C74159C9914D9B20CCA781C8CFEED29" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Salicaceae" genus="Populus" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Populus tremula" order="Malpighiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tremula">Populus tremula</taxonomicName>
) tree by using an eclector trap.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="A0FC0DE34AFD82C255F8699F07A7903B" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" type="conservation">
<paragraph id="032E167EC6BC3A3EC32B6E0E8AE17CC2" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">Conservation</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9BEB94BE4ECC49C0F353F6A00E0B0C03" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068">
The species was red-listed in Finland (EN, 
<bibRefCitation id="9EBD3A38F2768CD68C8D5B5869C8D43E" author="Penttinen, J." editor="Rassi, P." journalOrPublisher="Ympaeristoeministerioe &amp; Suomen ympaeristoekeskus, Helsinki" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="The 2010 Red List of Finnish Species" year="2010">Penttinen et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
) based on the single record from Savonranta. 
<taxonomicName id="39E725460E33348781FE309D1BF43349" class="Insecta" family="Mycetophilidae" genus="Sciophila" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Sciophila salassea" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="salassea">Sciophila salassea</taxonomicName>
is also red-listed in Norway (NT), so far observed from pristine spruce forests (
<bibRefCitation id="A28586D9665F948BEA85DB977E7BC9BF" author="Anonymous," journalOrPublisher="Artsdatabanken" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="Rodliste for arter 2010" year="2010">Anonymous 2010</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="464ABCF486A30F055E53C7A18B5AABA5" author="Gammelmo, O." editor="Kalas, A." journalOrPublisher="Norwegian Biodiversity Information Centre" pageId="0" pageNumber="1068" title="The 2010 Norwegian Red List for Species" year="2010">Gammelmo et al. 2010</bibRefCitation>
)
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
